## Overview

Establish the shared foundational layer required by the Google Maps feature (Issue #18). Creates a reusable debounce hook, the `MarkerData` TypeScript interface, and the `NEXT_PUBLIC_MAP_ID` environment variable entry.

## Files to Create / Modify

| Action | File | Notes |
|--------|------|-------|
| Create | `lib/useDebounce.ts` | Generic debounce hook |
| Create | `types/marker.ts` | `MarkerData` TypeScript interface |
| Modify | `.env.example` | Add `NEXT_PUBLIC_MAP_ID` entry |
| Modify | `types/index.ts` | Re-export `MarkerData` |

## Key Implementation Notes

### `lib/useDebounce.ts`
```ts
import { useState, useEffect } from 'react';
export function useDebounce<T>(value: T, delay: number): T {
  const [debouncedValue, setDebouncedValue] = useState<T>(value);
  useEffect(() => {
    const timer = setTimeout(() => setDebouncedValue(value), delay);
    return () => clearTimeout(timer);
  }, [value, delay]);
  return debouncedValue;
}
```

### `types/marker.ts`
```ts
export interface MarkerData {
  id: string;
  name: string;
  species: string;
  lat: number;
  lng: number;
  h3Index: string;
  lastEncounteredAt: string;
  imageUrl: string;
}
```
Fields match exactly what `GET /api/markers` returns (see `app/api/markers/route.ts` L131-L143).

### `.env.example` addition
```
# Google Maps Map ID (for AdvancedMarker support)
NEXT_PUBLIC_MAP_ID=                  # GCP → Maps → Map IDs → Create map ID with dark theme
```

## Acceptance Criteria
- [ ] `useDebounce<T>` exported from `lib/useDebounce.ts` with correct generic signature
- [ ] `MarkerData` exported from `types/marker.ts` and re-exported via `types/index.ts`
- [ ] `.env.example` contains `NEXT_PUBLIC_MAP_ID=` with descriptive comment
- [ ] No new runtime npm dependencies introduced

## Dependencies
None — foundational subissue, merge first.
